gomodel:SYNGO_499  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 5: HuD (ELAVL4) co-localises with Bdnf mRNA in hippocampal cultures transfected with recombinant GFP-mHuD at 14 DIV and stained using antisense probe against Bdnf. Furthermore knock-down of endogenous HuD in rat hippocampal cultures blocked the ability of PKC activation to increase dendritic translation of mRNAs with the long Bdnf 3' UTR.\n\n28/5/2018 Pim\n- Accepted in SynGO because BDNF is a synaptically active compound: \"Brain-derived neurotrophic factor (BDNF) is an important molecule involved in learning and memory in the adult brain, with demonstrated roles in regulating synaptic plasticity [1-3]. \". Experimental description: Sprague Dawley rats, both male and females" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2094-7491" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4419-210X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1190-4481" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9848-0262" ;
        dc:date           "2018-05-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_499" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

